WEBVTT

00:02.572 --> 00:04.074
Come on, Carl, step on it.

00:04.075 --> 00:05.742
Drive on the sidewalk
if you have to.

00:05.743 --> 00:08.077
Hey, I'm your partner...
I will get us there.

00:08.079 --> 00:10.113
But you should have just
used the bathroom at Abe's.

00:10.114 --> 00:12.482
I like going at my mom's house.

00:12.483 --> 00:13.917
She's at work, and it's quiet.

00:13.918 --> 00:15.452
Plus, I grew up
with that toilet.

00:15.453 --> 00:17.120
We know each other's secrets.

00:17.121 --> 00:18.755
Easy, easy!

00:18.756 --> 00:20.457
Stay with me, buddy.
We're almost there.

00:20.458 --> 00:22.125
Carl, I'm not gonna make it.

00:22.126 --> 00:23.726
Hey, d-don't you
let go on me, man!

00:23.727 --> 00:25.695
Don't you let go on me!

00:25.696 --> 00:27.863
(siren wailing)

00:29.532 --> 00:31.700
(toilet flushes)

00:33.503 --> 00:35.037
(screams)

00:35.772 --> 00:37.873
Mom, what are you doing home?

00:37.875 --> 00:38.875
I live here.

00:38.876 --> 00:40.443
What the hell are you doing?

00:40.444 --> 00:42.178
I came to borrow
your <i> Better Homes & Gardens.</i>

00:42.179 --> 00:44.480
What do you think?

00:44.481 --> 00:47.116
So you're the one who's been
Goldilocks-ing around my house

00:47.117 --> 00:48.451
while I've been at work.

00:48.452 --> 00:50.420
You know, if you're gonna nap
in somebody's bed,

00:50.421 --> 00:52.321
you need to make it
when you're done.

00:52.322 --> 00:53.790
I tried.

00:53.791 --> 00:55.790
You know I can't get
the corners as tight as you.

00:55.792 --> 00:57.659
No one can.

00:58.928 --> 01:01.030
Wait, what are you
doing home anyway?

01:01.031 --> 01:02.298
Shouldn't you be at work?

01:02.299 --> 01:03.799
What, are you my parole officer?

01:03.800 --> 01:07.203
I got to keep you updated on
my whereabouts and my doings?

01:07.204 --> 01:09.071
What? I'm just asking.

01:09.072 --> 01:10.839
I retired, okay?

01:10.841 --> 01:12.240
Since when?

01:12.242 --> 01:14.510
Since I decided to stop working.

01:14.511 --> 01:16.078
All these years
in the cafeteria,

01:16.079 --> 01:17.580
you just woke up
one day and decided,

01:17.581 --> 01:19.582
"I've sloppied my last joe."

01:19.583 --> 01:20.616
Maybe I did.

01:20.617 --> 01:21.584
What's it to you?

01:21.585 --> 01:22.551
I don't know.

01:22.552 --> 01:24.119
Maybe I want to say
congratulations.

01:24.121 --> 01:25.588
There, you said it.

01:25.589 --> 01:27.989
Now, unless you're gonna give me
a gold watch, beat it.

01:27.991 --> 01:29.992
All right, all right, I'm going.

01:29.993 --> 01:31.993
Leave the <i>Homes & Gardens.</i>

01:31.995 --> 01:34.028
I'm sick of you stealing
my magazines.

01:34.030 --> 01:36.265
Sorry, "Dr. Izzian Lahiri."

01:36.266 --> 01:37.266
Yeah.

01:37.267 --> 01:39.068
Hey, he's not gonna read it.

01:39.069 --> 01:41.235
He can barely speak English.

01:43.372 --> 01:44.707
(door closes)

01:44.708 --> 01:47.909
I hate my home,
and I don't have a garden.

01:49.044 --> 01:50.446
(both scream)

01:50.447 --> 01:51.479
Oh.

01:51.481 --> 01:52.614
Hey, Mama Biggs.

01:52.615 --> 01:54.348
What you doing home?

