Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:29.305 --> 07:31.573
This is a very nice party.

07:32.976 --> 07:35.110
Boy, you're easy to please.

07:35.979 --> 07:38.580
These canapés are
quite delightful.

07:38.582 --> 07:41.283
Did you need 12 of 'em
to decide that?

07:44.754 --> 07:47.522
So what are your plans now?

07:47.524 --> 07:49.825
Why does everybody
keep asking me that?

07:49.827 --> 07:52.862
Well, we are
at your retirement party.

07:52.863 --> 07:55.764
But I guess we can just
sit here in silence.

07:56.766 --> 07:58.701
I'll never retire.

07:58.702 --> 08:01.803
Three weeks after my pop stopped
working, he dropped dead.

08:01.805 --> 08:05.875
He was hiking the Grand Canyon
and didn't bring any water.

08:05.876 --> 08:08.043
I guess what I'm saying is...
hydrate.

08:09.178 --> 08:11.280
I hate the taste of water.

08:11.281 --> 08:12.781
Of course you do.

08:14.584 --> 08:15.952
You should hear
your mom out there.

08:15.953 --> 08:17.486
I think she actually believes
she retired.

08:17.487 --> 08:18.486
Molly, I'm telling you,

08:18.488 --> 08:20.456
in her little world,
she is retired,

08:20.457 --> 08:22.558
her podiatrist
is in love with her,

08:22.559 --> 08:25.361
and Anderson Cooper isn't gay.

08:25.362 --> 08:27.329
I can't imagine deluding
myself like that.

08:27.330 --> 08:29.331
I have to live honestly.

08:29.332 --> 08:30.666
Oh, really?

08:30.667 --> 08:32.534
So you were born
with that hair color?

08:32.535 --> 08:34.102
Yes.

08:34.104 --> 08:35.638
I was. That's...

08:35.639 --> 08:38.039
why I keep trying
to get back to it.

08:38.041 --> 08:41.743
And, uh, y-you were the one who
came up with "talk to the hand."

08:41.745 --> 08:45.648
Maybe not "came up with it,"
but I brought it to Chicago.

08:45.649 --> 08:47.583
Molly, look, I'm just...

08:47.584 --> 08:49.250
Ah-ah-ah-ah.

08:50.586 --> 08:52.555
It's great that you retired

08:52.556 --> 08:54.689
while you're still able
to enjoy...

08:56.525 --> 08:59.027
I'm sorry, is there
anything you enjoy?

08:59.029 --> 09:03.365
I've only ever really had
one passion... cooking.

09:03.366 --> 09:05.100
In bulk.

09:05.101 --> 09:07.635
Well, if that's the case, you
sure lucked into the right son.

09:07.637 --> 09:09.570
What are we talking about?

09:09.572 --> 09:12.741
About how happy
you make your mom.

09:12.742 --> 09:14.042
Yeah, he's one in a million.

09:14.043 --> 09:15.978
Always come to visit
when I'm not at home,

09:15.979 --> 09:18.512
and always tests the plumbing.

09:19.681 --> 09:21.016
Hey, now with your mom
being around,

09:21.017 --> 09:22.851
when we go over there
for your little bathroom breaks,

09:22.852 --> 09:23.951
we can stay for lunch, too.

09:23.953 --> 09:25.387
No, no, I like my routine.

09:25.388 --> 09:26.722
I eat lunch at Abe's,

09:26.723 --> 09:28.757
and that greasy food
sends me to my mother's.

09:28.758 --> 09:30.025
If I eat at Mom's,

09:30.026 --> 09:32.661
who knows where I'll
be when the muse hits.

09:32.662 --> 09:34.362
Hey, do you think
what's-his-name needs

09:34.363 --> 09:35.630
any help down at that diner?

09:35.631 --> 09:37.966
Maybe you could put in
a good word for me.

09:37.967 --> 09:39.267
To work at Abe's?

09:39.268 --> 09:40.868
Uh, n-n-no, y-you don't
want to do that.

09:40.870 --> 09:42.637
Why not?

09:42.638 --> 09:44.639
Because, as your tiara says,
you're retired.

09:44.640 --> 09:46.641
Enjoy your golden years.

09:46.642 --> 09:47.943
At home.

09:47.944 --> 09:50.311
Away from people.

09:50.313 --> 09:53.848
I took 18 stitches pushing
your big head out my cervix,

09:53.849 --> 09:56.217
and you can't do
something nice for me?

09:56.218 --> 09:57.885
What do you call this?

09:57.887 --> 09:59.387
Boring.

09:59.388 --> 10:00.522
These are all your friends.

10:00.523 --> 10:01.556
Where are mine?

10:01.557 --> 10:02.691
That's a good question, Ma.

10:02.692 --> 10:03.757
Where are your friends?

10:03.759 --> 10:05.760
What are you saying?
Nothing.

10:05.761 --> 10:08.263
Let's just get through
this joyous occasion.

10:08.264 --> 10:09.264
You ingrate.

10:09.265 --> 10:10.397
After all I've done for you,

10:10.399 --> 10:12.333
you can't put in
a good word for me

10:12.334 --> 10:13.735
at that crappy diner?

10:13.736 --> 10:15.437
Oh, believe me, Ma,
if I could find a good word,

10:15.438 --> 10:16.403
I'd put it in.

10:16.405 --> 10:18.505
What is that supposed to mean?

10:18.507 --> 10:20.575
It means I don't want
to subject my friends

10:20.576 --> 10:21.742
to the Griddler, either.

10:21.744 --> 10:24.244
I know about the cafeteria.

10:24.246 --> 10:25.547
You got fired.

10:25.548 --> 10:27.115
As usual, you don't know squat.

10:27.116 --> 10:28.449
I retired.

10:28.450 --> 10:30.651
And if somebody tells you
different, they're liars.

10:30.653 --> 10:31.986
No!

10:31.987 --> 10:33.120
You're the liar!

10:33.122 --> 10:34.856
You always have been!

10:34.857 --> 10:37.558
You got fired because
you're bitter and toxic

10:37.559 --> 10:39.626
and nobody wants
to be around you.

10:41.028 --> 10:43.731
♪ For she's a jolly
good fellow ♪

10:43.732 --> 10:46.134
♪ For she's a jolly... ♪

10:46.135 --> 10:47.968
You and I are done.

10:52.340 --> 10:54.141
What happened?

10:54.142 --> 10:55.576
Mike just told off his mom.

10:55.577 --> 10:58.678
Oh, and I missed it?

11:09.137 --> 11:11.672
Let's not overdo it
with the coffee, Samuel.

11:11.673 --> 11:13.641
I don't know where
I'm landing after this lunch.

11:13.642 --> 11:15.009
Come on.

11:15.010 --> 11:16.543
Your mom's house is
right on our beat.

11:16.545 --> 11:17.545
Nope.

11:17.546 --> 11:19.980
That commode is dead to me.

11:19.982 --> 11:22.350
Ah, you should
appreciate your mother.

11:22.351 --> 11:23.951
Mine is 4,000 miles away,

11:23.952 --> 11:25.953
but I can still feel her love
every day,

11:25.954 --> 11:27.488
like she's right beside me.

11:27.489 --> 11:28.990
Supporting me, comforting me,

11:28.991 --> 11:31.759
making me feel like I'm the most
important person in the world.

11:31.760 --> 11:33.960
Yeah, well, the one they gave me
doesn't do that.

11:35.496 --> 11:36.831
You know, the only thing
that kept me

11:36.832 --> 11:38.299
in that abusive
relationship so long

11:38.300 --> 11:39.834
was because of her cooking.

11:39.835 --> 11:42.136
You know?
She'd-she'd treat me like crap,

11:42.137 --> 11:44.438
and then think a five-cheese
macaroni casserole

11:44.439 --> 11:45.740
was gonna make it all better.

11:45.741 --> 11:48.708
And it did.

11:48.710 --> 11:50.978
Mike, you can't let this
go on forever.

11:50.979 --> 11:52.112
Okay? She's your mother.

11:52.114 --> 11:53.514
Yeah, well, if you're
so in love with her,

11:53.515 --> 11:54.548
you can give her a call.

11:54.549 --> 11:55.783
You know what started
this whole thing?

11:55.784 --> 11:58.052
She asked me to help
get her a job. Here.

11:58.053 --> 11:59.053
Seriously?

11:59.054 --> 12:00.254
What did you tell her?

12:00.255 --> 12:01.322
I can't have her working here.

12:01.323 --> 12:02.589
That woman is toxic.

12:05.225 --> 12:09.062
(man chanting in Latin)

12:16.804 --> 12:18.839
Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

12:18.840 --> 12:21.408
It's been five days
since my last confession.

12:21.409 --> 12:23.610
Go ahead, my child.

12:23.611 --> 12:25.878
Father, this is
very hard for me.

12:25.880 --> 12:29.149
How does a good-hearted person
who only means well

12:29.150 --> 12:31.618
become so prideful
and pigheaded?

12:31.619 --> 12:33.220
Well, we are all weak.

12:33.221 --> 12:34.554
But what is important

12:34.555 --> 12:35.989
is that you're
acknowledging your mistakes

12:35.990 --> 12:37.758
and are willing to repent.

12:37.759 --> 12:39.626
I'm not talking about me.

12:39.627 --> 12:41.927
It's my ungrateful son.

12:41.929 --> 12:44.965
I sacrificed everything
for that boy,

12:44.966 --> 12:46.366
and how does he pay me back?

12:46.367 --> 12:49.236
By saying I'm toxic
and horrible to be around.

12:49.237 --> 12:50.536
Can you believe that?

12:50.538 --> 12:54.174
That he would say it, or...?

12:54.175 --> 12:57.010
I'm not quite sure
what you're confessing.

12:57.011 --> 12:58.044
(sighs)

12:58.045 --> 13:01.448
I guess the sin of
thinking my only child

13:01.449 --> 13:04.484
might appreciate
all that I've done for him.

13:04.485 --> 13:05.852
That's not a sin.

13:05.853 --> 13:07.387
That just sounds
like being needy.

13:07.388 --> 13:10.290
Hey, I came here
for your absolution,

13:10.291 --> 13:11.458
not your opinion.

13:11.459 --> 13:13.259
Yes, but I can't
absolve you of anything

13:13.260 --> 13:14.861
if nothing's your fault.

13:14.862 --> 13:17.731
I'd like to talk
to your supervisor.

13:17.732 --> 13:19.265
Is the monsignor around?

13:19.266 --> 13:20.467
He's on a retreat, Peggy.

13:20.468 --> 13:22.102
It's just me.

13:22.103 --> 13:24.571
Well, then, maybe you need
to look at yourself.

13:24.572 --> 13:26.706
"Judge not, lest ye be judged."

13:26.707 --> 13:27.840
Matthew 7:1.

13:27.842 --> 13:29.943
"First take the log
out of your own eye,

13:29.944 --> 13:31.444
and then you will see clearly."

13:31.445 --> 13:33.413
Matthew 7:5.

13:33.414 --> 13:36.182
"Thou shalt not covet
thy parish's choir director."

13:36.183 --> 13:38.451
Book of Peggy,
chapter one, verse one,

13:38.452 --> 13:41.621
phone call to the archdiocese.

13:41.622 --> 13:43.656
We're done here.

13:43.657 --> 13:44.991
Hey, if you can't
stand the heat,

13:44.992 --> 13:46.692
stay out of the box!

13:51.831 --> 13:54.332
(sports commentator
speaking over TV)

13:56.969 --> 13:57.937
Hey.

13:57.938 --> 13:59.038
How you doing?

13:59.039 --> 14:00.006
Good.

14:00.007 --> 14:01.407
Just watching the hockey game.

14:01.408 --> 14:04.777
Well, it's not the same
watching it without your mom.

14:04.778 --> 14:05.711
You're right.

14:05.712 --> 14:09.347
It is so much better.

14:09.349 --> 14:10.983
Come on.
What?

14:10.984 --> 14:12.585
It's quieter, it's less tense.

14:12.586 --> 14:16.155
Nobody's calling me a jinx
when the other team scores.

14:16.156 --> 14:19.491
Mike, I know that your...

14:19.493 --> 14:21.927
mother can be unpleasant,

14:21.928 --> 14:24.563
and abrasive, and manipulative,

14:24.564 --> 14:29.468
and vindictive,
and a liar, but...

14:29.469 --> 14:31.036
I mean, there has to be

14:31.037 --> 14:32.837
another side.

14:34.106 --> 14:36.274
There has to be.

14:39.645 --> 14:42.181
Baby, you haven't talked to
her in a week and a half.

14:42.182 --> 14:43.682
Are you gonna tell me that...

14:43.683 --> 14:45.117
that doesn't bother you at all?

14:45.118 --> 14:46.584
Honestly, I'm fine with it.

14:46.586 --> 14:49.054
I slept nine full hours
last night.

14:49.055 --> 14:50.489
I didn't grind my teeth.

14:50.490 --> 14:53.192
I dreamt I could fly.

14:53.193 --> 14:55.594
I mean, you know,
I-I don't know what's going on,

14:55.595 --> 14:57.196
but I-I couldn't be happier.

14:57.197 --> 14:58.464
You're just riding the high

14:58.465 --> 15:00.065
off of telling off
your horrible mother,

15:00.066 --> 15:02.468
which I still can't
believe I missed, but...

15:02.469 --> 15:03.669
(sighs)

15:03.670 --> 15:05.170
It's time to make this right.

15:05.171 --> 15:06.638
I don't have to make it right.

15:06.639 --> 15:08.006
This is right.

15:08.007 --> 15:09.708
Like when I quit
eating spicy food

15:09.709 --> 15:11.076
and my heartburn went away.

15:11.077 --> 15:13.445
Now that she's gone,
no more acid burps.

15:13.446 --> 15:14.880
You know what?

15:14.881 --> 15:17.716
I'll bet I could go back
to eating Mexican food.

15:17.717 --> 15:19.418
So, what?

15:19.419 --> 15:21.753
You're never gonna talk
to your mother again?

15:21.754 --> 15:25.289
I'm not committing to nothing
until I eat a plate of nachos.

15:30.896 --> 15:33.097
(doorbell ringing)

15:34.800 --> 15:36.802
Hey.

15:36.803 --> 15:40.772
Just so you know, by marriage
you're dead to me, too.

15:40.773 --> 15:43.508
Peggy, I know you're upset.

15:43.509 --> 15:44.709
Of course I am.

15:44.710 --> 15:46.044
My son humiliated me

15:46.045 --> 15:47.512
at my own retirement party.

15:47.513 --> 15:50.248
Because you didn't
actually retire.

15:50.249 --> 15:51.715
What do you know?

15:51.717 --> 15:53.952
I talked to the ladies
you used to work with

15:53.953 --> 15:56.321
when I invited them to
your retirement party.

15:56.322 --> 15:57.322
Which Mike ruined.

15:57.323 --> 16:00.392
Because you're not
really retired!

16:00.393 --> 16:03.027
Okay? We are going
round and round here.

16:03.028 --> 16:05.563
Why don't you go round
and round and out that door?

16:05.564 --> 16:06.731
Okay, fine.

16:06.732 --> 16:07.799
I'll leave.
But you know what?

16:07.800 --> 16:09.033
I'm gonna say something first.

16:09.034 --> 16:10.602
If you spend your entire life

16:10.603 --> 16:13.104
thinking that everyone
you meet is the problem,

16:13.105 --> 16:15.340
it just might be you
that's the problem.

16:15.341 --> 16:17.175
Now you sound like my priest.

16:17.176 --> 16:18.510
And the mailman.

16:18.511 --> 16:19.811
And that idiot at the deli.

16:19.812 --> 16:20.945
I don't need a number.

16:20.946 --> 16:22.981
I know who I was in front of.

16:22.982 --> 16:25.149
Okay, maybe I'm wrong.

16:25.150 --> 16:27.919
Maybe it is
everyone else's fault.

16:27.920 --> 16:29.554
That's what I've been saying!

16:29.555 --> 16:32.390
(exhales)

16:32.391 --> 16:34.759
Look, Peggy, I get it.

16:34.760 --> 16:35.993
Okay? I'm stubborn, too.

16:35.994 --> 16:37.295
Damn right you are.

16:37.296 --> 16:38.496
And a bad cook.

16:38.497 --> 16:40.565
I like where this is going.

16:40.566 --> 16:43.267
The point is that

16:43.268 --> 16:46.337
I have learned to
admit when I'm wrong

16:46.338 --> 16:48.806
and to accept
responsibility for it.

16:48.807 --> 16:50.941
'Cause I'd rather
be wrong and loved

16:50.943 --> 16:53.243
than stubborn and alone.

16:55.279 --> 16:57.348
Is any of this landing?

16:57.349 --> 16:59.349
'Cause I-I can't
read that scowl.

17:00.217 --> 17:02.319
I heard you.

17:02.320 --> 17:04.922
Well, then, call your son.

17:04.923 --> 17:06.424
Trust me, you'll feel better.

17:06.425 --> 17:09.425
From one stubborn gal
to another.

17:10.227 --> 17:12.262
You know what?

17:12.263 --> 17:13.631
You're right.

17:13.632 --> 17:15.499
You and I aren't so different.

17:15.500 --> 17:18.502
I don't know if I'd go that far.

17:18.502 --> 17:19.837
Stubborn,

17:19.838 --> 17:22.006
always have to get our own way,

17:22.007 --> 17:24.108
madly in love with my boy...

17:24.108 --> 17:26.010
Ew.

17:26.011 --> 17:27.877
I guess what they say is true.

17:27.878 --> 17:31.047
Sons do grow up
to marry their mothers.

17:31.982 --> 17:33.983
That's not true.

17:34.918 --> 17:37.053
God, that can't be true.

17:46.354 --> 17:48.490
♪ For she's a jolly
good fellow ♪

17:48.491 --> 17:51.625
♪ Which nobody can deny. ♪

17:51.627 --> 17:53.228
This is so much better.

17:53.229 --> 17:55.162
More intimate,
not so many strangers.

17:55.164 --> 17:57.999
Well, those strangers
were my family.

17:58.000 --> 17:59.233
I didn't mean that.

17:59.234 --> 18:01.602
I meant strange, as in weird.

18:02.737 --> 18:04.505
This is the knife
you got to cut the cake?

18:04.506 --> 18:06.240
You told me to grab the one
off the counter.

18:06.241 --> 18:07.575
Never mind.

18:07.576 --> 18:09.943
I'm surprised you didn't
grab the can opener.

18:12.547 --> 18:13.548
See?

18:13.549 --> 18:16.217
This is nice.

18:16.218 --> 18:17.452
I'm sorry.

18:17.453 --> 18:19.120
I should have let you enjoy
your motherless high

18:19.121 --> 18:20.755
for a few more weeks.

18:20.756 --> 18:22.056
I got a taste.

18:22.057 --> 18:25.226
I should be good
for another 35 years.

18:25.227 --> 18:26.494
I can't believe
I actually thought

18:26.495 --> 18:28.062
she was gonna apologize to you.

18:28.063 --> 18:30.164
Ah, she did in her own way.

18:30.165 --> 18:32.366
Usually, she'd rub something
like this in my face.

18:32.367 --> 18:34.769
Now she's pretending
like it didn't even happen,

18:34.770 --> 18:37.171
which is a big step for her.

18:37.172 --> 18:39.172
Now we can cut the cake.

18:39.174 --> 18:40.608
That is the same knife.

18:40.609 --> 18:41.609
It's a different knife.

18:41.610 --> 18:42.576
She's retired.

18:42.577 --> 18:44.744
Live the lie.

18:44.746 --> 18:47.181
How about a big corner piece
for my boy?

18:47.182 --> 18:48.582
Not too big.

18:48.583 --> 18:50.357
All of a sudden
I got really bad heartburn.

